# Plan: ~/llm — Modular LLM Workspace Migration

## Problem

Everything lives in `~/copilot` as a monolithic, non-shareable, user-specific tree. Agent definitions, personal config, secrets references, runtime output, and dev experiments are all mixed together with hardcoded values throughout. It can't be shared with a team, onboarded to, or maintained modularly.

## Approach

Build a fresh **4-directory structure** under `~/llm/` — copying and refactoring content from `~/copilot/` (which remains untouched). Extract hardcoded values into environment files. Make the core workspace git-shareable.

---

