## env/AGENTS.md — Security & Load Order

```markdown
# LLM Environment — Load Order & Security

## Load Order
1. Read `.env` — non-sensitive configuration (paths, org names, iterations)
2. Read `profile.md` — identity, preferences, repo list
3. NEVER read `.secrets` into LLM context or output

## .secrets Handling
- Scripts may source .secrets to retrieve Keeper UIDs
- The LLM must NEVER print, echo, or include .secrets content in responses
- If a secret is needed, instruct the user to run a script or use `$KSM_BINARY`

## File Purposes
| File | Contains | Git-tracked | LLM reads |
|------|----------|-------------|-----------|
| .env | Paths, org names, API versions | Yes | Yes |
| .secrets | Keeper UIDs, PAT retrieval info | NO | NO |
| profile.md | Identity, preferences, repos | Yes | Yes |
| keeper.ini | KSM local config | NO | NO |
```

