## Decisions Log

| Decision | Choice | Rationale |
|---|---|---|
| Parent structure | `~/llm/` with 4 subdirs | Keeps all LLM concerns together, avoids `~` clutter |
| Naming | workspace, env, sandbox, output | workspace=shared system, env=user config, sandbox=experiments, output=runtime |
| {insert-team-tag} identity | Dissolved into agents + env | "{insert-team-tag}" was conflating identity, ADO, vaults, and sessions |
| Feedback loop | Hook, not agent | It's a behavioral trigger, not a standalone capability |
| personal/ projects | → sandbox/ | Personal dev work belongs in the playground |
| Module system release | → plugin_lib/ | Released/shared code belongs in the workspace |
| Output location | ~/llm/output/ (not in workspace or env) | Clean separation: system, config, experiments, artifacts |
| Sandbox git | TBD by user | Not our call to over-architect |
| Scripts | Read env vars, not hardcoded paths | Enables team sharing |

## Notes

- `~/copilot/` is NOT touched — this is a copy-and-refactor operation
- All AGENTS.md files should be concise (token-efficient) — verbose explanations go in docs/
- The `llm_module_upgrade` agent is critical — it's the self-referential "how to change this system" guide
- `env/.secrets` is NEVER read by the LLM — scripts can source it, humans can read it, but the LLM must not include it in context or output
